<h1 class="display-6">
    Conditional (ternary) operator
</h1>
<div class="container">
    <div class="container">
        <p>
            <code>condition ? true : false</code>
        </p>
        <p>
            Given three variables <code>a</code>, <code>b</code> and <code>c</code>, 
            write a program that adds <br> <code>a * 5</code> + <code>b * 10</code> + <code>c * 20</code>. 
        </p>
        <p>
            If any of the given variables are negative, return <code>"invalid"</code>.
        </p>
        <pre><code class="lang-js">
function scoreCalculator(a, b, c) {
	return a >= 0 && b >= 0 && c >= 0 ?
	  a * 5 + b * 10 + c * 20 : "invalid";
}       
        </code></pre>
        <p>
            In the example above, if any of the variables 
            are negative "invalid", or the false condition, is returned. 
            If all of them are positive, however, the variables 
            are multiplied and added together.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>